  <div class="faq__row">
    <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
    <ul class="faq__list">
      <li>
        <p class="faq__toggle">
          Is custom more expensive than ready-made jewelry?
        </p>
        <p class="faq__answer">
          Doing all of our work in-house, allows us to control costs and craft you an exquisite piece of jewelry at a
          fair price. Pricing is based on design complexity, metal, and gemstones. Quotes are 100% free.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="faq__toggle">
          How long does it take to complete a custom project?
        </p>
        <p class="faq__answer">
          The time it takes to finish a custom project can vary greatly, with a turnaround time of 4-6 weeks for a
          standard design and 6-8 weeks for a more complex model. Let us know if there is an important event on the
          horizon and we will do our best to accommodate you! </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="faq__toggle">
          Can I recycle my old gold into my new custom piece?
        </p>
        <p class="faq__answer">
          We can absolutely recycle heirloom gemstones into your new jewelry, it’s what we excel at! Recycling “used”
          gold for a new casting frequently creates pieces with blemishes and pitting that affects the finish and
          strength of the piece. We only use refined casting grain so we can be confident that your jewelry will
          withstand the test of time. Old metal can be scrapped and credited towards the cost of your custom piece. </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="faq__toggle">
          Does my custom jewelry come with an appraisal?
        </p>
        <p class="faq__answer">
          Yes. Every custom piece of jewelry comes with an insurance replacement document, completed by one of our
          GIA-trained graduate gemologists. </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="faq__toggle">
          Do you offer a warranty?
        </p>
        <p class="faq__answer">
          No other jeweler in the industry promises what we do. Jewelry is meant to be worn. It becomes a part of you
          going down all of life’s bumpy paths. We will stand by your bridal jewelry with cleanings, inspections, and
          even repairs due to normal wear - at no cost to you.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
